  "prompt": "Have people been told by \"seller agents\" to not use Redfin?",
  "response": "Yes, there have been instances where some traditional real estate agents have advised clients not to use Redfin or similar online real estate platforms. This often stems from various reasons, including criticisms of the technology-driven model that Redfin employs, concerns about the level of personal service provided, or differing commission structures.\n\nTraditional agents may feel that using platforms like Redfin could undermine their business models or lead to less personalized service. However, opinions on this matter vary widely, and many consumers find significant value in using technology-driven services for their real estate needs.\n\nIf you're considering buying or selling a home, it's essential to research and choose the option that best fits your needs, whether that\u2019s a traditional agent, an online service, or a hybrid approach.",
